<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE6416BCB1CEE3BFE6D2714" author="Glenn, G. S. Jr." box="[346,479,1879,1905]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" pagination="67 - 102" refId="ref16270" refString="Glenn, G. S. Jr. (1991) A systematic revision of Enyaliopsis Karsch 1887 (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae, Hetrodinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 117, 67 - 102. http: // www. jstor. org / stable / 25078540" type="journal article" year="1991">Glenn 1991</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE6416BCBADEE3BFDDC2714" author="Hemp, C." box="[491,622,1879,1905]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" refId="ref16956" refString="Hemp, C. (2021) A Field Guide to the Bushcrickets, Wetas and Raspy Crickets of Tanzania and Kenya. Senckenberg Gesellschaft fur Naturforschung, Frankfurt, 451 pp." type="book" year="2021">Hemp 2021</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE6416BCA81EE16FE0B27B8" blockId="16.[151,1436,1806,2013]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE6416BCA81EE16FED027F1" bold="true" box="[199,354,1914,1940]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Bioacoustics.</emphasis>
Tegmina (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE6416BCB9FEE17FDAE27F0" box="[473,540,1915,1941]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[161,1415,290,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-72@5.[151,1436,273,1718]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Left male tegmina of Acanthoplus discoidalis (CH8946), Acanthoproctus cervinus (CH8947), Hetrodes pupus (CHelb8948), Enyaliopsis bloyeti (CH8853), E. carolinus (CH8625), E. ephippiatus (CH7737), E. jennae (damaged; CH8267), Gymnoproctus rammei (CH8763), Eugasteroides loricatus (CH7352), Spalacomimus stettinenesis, S. talpa (CH7354), S. verruciferus (CH7188). Scale 5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392715" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392715/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), stridulatory file (
<tableCitation id="1A7D036FFFE6416BC8A8EE17FCF027F0" box="[750,834,1915,1941]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,239,332,356]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="TABLE 1. Body dimensions and characteristics of stridulatory files in Hetrodini" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0380665CFFF54178CAD1E820FC402101" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" tableUuid="0380665CFFF54178CAD1E820FC402101">Table 1</tableCitation>
), and spectrum of the song (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE6416BCEC5EE17FB7427F3" box="[1155,1222,1915,1942]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1287,1311]" captionTargetBox="[171,1410,201,1247]" captionTargetId="figure-23@10.[151,1436,181,1263]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Power spectra of male calling songs in Hetrodini species" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392725" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392725/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
) do not show large differences to the typical 
<taxonomicName id="90FF4D57FFE6416BCBF6EEF3FDA927DC" authorityName=", Kowalski &amp; Lakes-Harlan" authorityYear="2010" box="[432,539,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Hetrodini">Hetrodini</taxonomicName>
pattern. The calling song (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE6416BC905EEF3FC2B27DC" box="[835,921,1951,1977]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1216,1240]" captionTargetBox="[154,1428,204,1175]" captionTargetId="figure-23@12.[151,1436,181,1192]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 8. Oscillograms of the calling songs in the genera Cosmoderus and Enyaliopsis (figures of E. iaculator based on figures and data from literature; see text). A Cosmoderus femoratus, B Enyaliopsis bloyeti. C Enyaliopsis carolinus, D Enyaliopsis ephippiatus, song type A, E Enyaliopsis spec. 1 (near ephippiatus), song type B, F Enyaliopsis iaculator, G Enyaliopsis jennae, H Enyaliopsis spec. 2 Mpwapwa. Left column overview (5-s-section), right column detail (250-ms-section)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392733/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Fig. 8G</figureCitation>
) consists of long series of syllables (song 
<typeStatus id="88448876FFE6416BCF2AEEF3FA2E27DC" box="[1388,1436,1951,1977]" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">type</typeStatus>
B 
<quantity id="90079B31FFE6416BCAECEEAFFF6727B8" box="[170,213,1987,2013]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE6416BCA9AEEAFFEAD27B8" box="[220,287,1986,2013]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1254,1278]" captionTargetBox="[158,1423,198,1221]" captionTargetId="figure-23@8.[151,1436,181,1231]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Oscillograms of song types in Hetrodini. Song consisting A of long trills (Cosmoderus femoralis CH8627), B of broken trills (including transitions to long echemes; B1 Spalacomimus talpa, B2 Enyaliopsis jennae, B3 Enyaliopsis ephippiatus) or C of regularly repeated echemes (C1 Spalacomimus spec. near verruciferus, C2 Eugaster guyoni). 1-min-sections." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392721/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="467">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
; see 
<tableCitation id="1A7D036FFFE6416BCB10EEAFFE1E27B8" box="[342,428,1987,2013]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="7.[151,236,476,501]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 2. Song characteristics of Hetrodini species (for song type see Fig. 5 and text)" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190" pageId="16" pageNumber="467" tableUuid="0380665CFFF1417CCAD1E8B0FBBD2190">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE7416ACA81E9FAFA9A20D4" blockId="17.[151,1436,150,285]" box="[199,1320,150,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE7416ACA81E9FAFE8F20D5" bold="true" box="[199,317,150,176]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Genitalia.</emphasis>
The titillator of our specimen (
<figureCitation id="CFC42A51FFE7416AC8DDE9FBFD5C20D4" box="[667,750,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1200,1224]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,237,1177]" captionTargetId="figure-41@13.[151,1436,237,1179]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 9. Titillator and genitalic sclerites in Hetrodini, Enyaliopsina. First row A Cosmoderus femoralis (CH8627), B Enyaliopsis bloyeti (Kazimzumbwi), C Enyaliopsis carolinus (Minziro), D Enyaliopsis ephippiatus (Rau Forest); second row E Enyaliopsis spec. 1 near ephippiatus (Mwala), F Enyaliopsis jennae (Uluguru), G Enyaliopsis spec. 2 (Mpwapwa), H Enyaliopsis spec. 3 (East Chenene); third row I Gymnoproctus rammei (Puge Simbo), J Gymnoproctus spec. (East Chenene)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6392735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6392735/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
) agrees quite well with the figure in 
<bibRefCitation id="336E4B25FFE7416ACECCE9FBFA9620D4" author="Glenn, G. S. Jr." box="[1162,1316,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468" pagination="67 - 102" refId="ref16270" refString="Glenn, G. S. Jr. (1991) A systematic revision of Enyaliopsis Karsch 1887 (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae, Hetrodinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 117, 67 - 102. http: // www. jstor. org / stable / 25078540" type="journal article" year="1991">Glenn (1991)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="574036D4FFE7416ACA81E9D6FC922178" blockId="17.[151,1436,150,285]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">
<emphasis id="658BEAC6FFE7416ACA81E9D6FEC920B1" bold="true" box="[199,379,186,212]" pageId="17" pageNumber="468">Chromosomes:</emphasis>
2n = 28 (26 + neo-XY), FN = 29; pairs 1–13 acrocentric, longest in the set metacentric neo-X and long acrocentric neo-Y (
